      "content": "Powerhouse's software architecture has three layers:\n\n1. **Data Infrastructure Layer** -- handles secure storage and synchronization across local, cloud, and decentralized systems. Includes the Reactor (storage node) and network components (event buses, queues, caching, load balancers).\n2. **Host Application Layer** -- provides modular host applications (Connect, Switchboard, Fusion, Renown, Academy) that gain functionality through plugins.\n3. **Customization Layer** -- organization-specific plugins and instances enabling bespoke solutions for each network organization.",
